title: Czarnowo Wielkie
content:
Czarnowo Wielkie [t͡ʂarˈnɔvɔ ˈvjɛlkʲɛ] is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Gołdap, within Gołdap County, Warmian-Masurian Voivodeship, in northern Poland, close to the border with the Kaliningrad Oblast of Russia.[1] It lies approximately 10 kilometres (6 mi) east of Gołdap and 141 km (88 mi) north-east of the regional capital Olsztyn.
